  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Lucia Weston says that John A. Collins &quot;has had numberless troubles&quot; on account of the health of his family and a lack of money. John A. Collins, William Lloyd Garrison, Philemon Russell, and Oliver Johnson went to Acton &quot;to save Middlesex County.&quot; Lucia obtained from Garrison an account of what occurred there. She tells of the excitement caused by the controversy over the women&apos;s vote. Orange Scott called for all who favored a new organization to retire to a room below. &quot;They abused the Dr. [Amos Farnsworth] and the women openly.&quot;</subfield>
